qas.question: At what date did the name Seattle first appear on official papers?
When were the first land allocations made in Seattle?
At what date was Seattle incorporated as a town?
What type of governing body did Seattle have in 1869?
What famous Indian appears on the seal of Seattle?

context: The name "Seattle" appears on official Washington Territory papers dated <a0_0><a1_0>May 23, 1853<a1_0/><a0_0/>, when the first plats for the village were filed. In 1855, nominal land settlements were established. On <a2_0>January 14, 1865<a2_0/>, the Legislature of Territorial Washington incorporated the Town of Seattle with a board of trustees managing the city. The town of Seattle was disincorporated January 18, 1867 and remained a mere precinct of King County until late 1869, when a new petition was filed and the city was re-incorporated December 2, 1869 with a <a3_0>Mayor-council<a3_0/> government. The corporate seal of the City of Seattle carries the date "1869" and a likeness of <a4_0>Chief Sealth<a4_0/> in left profile.
